/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:42:      "`redeemInternal` calls `withdrawUSDTfromCmp(...)`, but `redeemUnderlying` fails or returns insufficient funds and the failure is ignored.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:44:      "The contract still subtracts the full `redeemTokens` from `totalSupply` and the user balance, then transfers only the reduced USDT amount."
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:64:    "claim": "All live USDT->USDC Curve swaps pass `_expected = 0` into the registry exchange call. That means borrow conversions and over-repayment refunds accept any output amount, with no slippage bound enforced by the caller.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:65:    "impact": "Searchers can sandwich these swaps and extract value by manipulating the Curve pool around the transaction. On borrows, the protocol records the full USDT debt while the lev side may receive materially less USDC than intended; on refund paths, excess repayment returned to the lev side can be skimmed the same way.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:67:      "Observe a borrow or repay/liquidation transaction that will trigger `changeUSDT2USDC`.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:68:      "Front-run to move the Curve USDT/USDC price against the protocol.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:82:    "title": "Ignored Compound mint errors can brick later USDT resupply attempts via stale allowance",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:91:    "claim": "`supplyUSDT2Cmp` uses `safeApprove` and then ignores the return code from cUSDT `mint(amount)`. If Compound returns a non-zero error code without consuming the approval, the USDT allowance from the market to cUSDT stays non-zero. Every later call to `supplyUSDT2Cmp` then reverts inside `safeApprove` because it forbids changing a non-zero allowance directly to another non-zero value.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:92:    "impact": "A single failed Compound supply can make later deposit or repay paths that try to re-supply idle USDT revert until someone manually resets the approval, causing operational DoS and trapping cash management in a broken state.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:94:      "A mint or repay path reaches `supplyUSDT2Cmp` with excess USDT.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:95:      "cUSDT `mint(amount)` returns an error code instead of reverting and does not spend the approved allowance.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:96:      "The non-zero USDT allowance to cUSDT remains in place.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/depusdt_levusdc_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:97:      "The next call into `supplyUSDT2Cmp` reverts on `SafeERC20: approve from non-zero to non-zero allowance`."
